The paper deals with the Virtual Network Embedding Problem (VNEP), which is a problem related to network infrastructure and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions latency constraints and routing policies, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Lastly, the paper discusses the embedding of service function chains, which is related to system integration, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
